is there a difference between these harry potter books is there a difference between the british adult versions and the american versions the american versions don't specify adult or children's like the brisiths ones do so is the british adult version different i've answered this question before and just copied by answer from before and pasted it below the only difference really is that in some scenes in the american version have a little more detail like in the first book during the sorting it mentions dean thomas a black boy but in the uk edition this part is left out here's the actual passage i found online three people left to be sorted 'turpin lisa' became uk edition three people left to be sorted thomas dean a black boy even taller than ron joined harry at the gryffindor table turpin us edition also some vocabulary words are different like torch would become flashlight in the us edition just little words like that are changed so we americans can understand what they are talking about here are some links that explain some more of the differences http www hp lexicon org about books differences html http www uta fi fast us ref potter html hope this helps Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban Hogwarts Houses Harry Potter Harry Potter and the Order of the Phoenix Gryffindors in Harry Potter's year Ginny Weasley Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban (film) Magical objects in Harry Potter Harry Potter (character) Hermione Granger Minor Hufflepuffs Uniform Resource Locator Minor characters associated with Quidditch Hogwarts Minor Slytherins Tao Te Ching African American Vernacular English Dictionary HyperText Transfer Protocol Ron Weasley Harry Potter: Book Seven World Wide Web Harry Potter and the Philosopher's Stone Harry Potter and the Chamber of Secrets American English Dates in Harry Potter Harry Potter and the Goblet of Fire HTML Metaphysics Autism Rubeus Hagrid Money in Harry Potter Neville Longbottom Theory of conduct Tetragrammaton James and Lily Potter